PROSECUTOR YOSHIKAZU YAGAWA

28:17.166 --> 28:19.000
SUICIDE NOTE OF DECEASED EMPLOYEE REVEALED

28:45.125 --> 28:46.333
Good morning.

28:50.291 --> 28:52.291
Good morning. Thank you!

28:53.666 --> 28:55.833
-Congratulations.
-Congratulations.

28:55.916 --> 28:56.958
Thank you.

28:57.041 --> 29:00.166
You did it. Other papers
are sure to rush in to chase it too.

29:01.708 --> 29:04.333
Ms. Matsuda, it's going viral
on social media.

29:04.416 --> 29:08.250
They can't ignore it now.
The administration will fall for sure.

29:08.791 --> 29:10.708
It hasn't worked out that way before.

29:11.541 --> 29:13.958
Maybe so, but this time
it's sure to happen.

29:14.041 --> 29:16.500
There's no doubt
the PM's office will respond.

29:17.291 --> 29:20.333
You'll probably be targeted again.

29:24.958 --> 29:28.375
I'll be fine.
This is when the real fight begins.

29:45.916 --> 29:48.541
Hello. It's been a while.

29:49.583 --> 29:51.583
I've got something I'd like to ask you.

29:53.541 --> 29:57.083
<i>The handwritten suicide note states that</i>
<i>Finance Bureau Director-General Mouri</i>

29:57.583 --> 30:01.291
<i>gave orders to alter documents</i>
<i>three times.</i>

30:01.833 --> 30:03.541
<i>It reveals information</i>
<i>not in the Ministry…</i>

30:16.666 --> 30:18.291
Thank you for calling.

30:18.375 --> 30:21.291
How are you doing?
Getting along all right?

30:22.958 --> 30:23.916
Yes, I am.

30:24.458 --> 30:28.208
<i>As I'm sure you know,</i>
<i>the Eishin affair has become big news.</i>

30:29.958 --> 30:32.416
Yes, I am aware of it.

30:33.666 --> 30:34.625
It's possible

30:36.333 --> 30:38.083
the prosecutor's office might investigate.

30:40.333 --> 30:43.250
What should I do?

30:44.208 --> 30:46.666
<i>It won't be easy,</i>
<i>but don't worry about it.</i>

30:47.916 --> 30:49.666
<i>Keep doing as you've done until now.</i>

30:53.125 --> 30:54.208
Are you sure?

30:55.125 --> 30:55.958
What's wrong?

30:59.041 --> 31:01.041
Do you plan on changing your testimony?

31:02.958 --> 31:03.958
<i>No.</i>

31:06.958 --> 31:07.916
Don't worry.

31:10.666 --> 31:13.541
The government certainly won't allow
any evidence to get out.

31:13.625 --> 31:17.208
But if some unexpected evidence
were found,

31:19.583 --> 31:21.875
the government would protect me, right?

31:23.125 --> 31:24.208
<i>Of course.</i>

31:25.458 --> 31:29.833
<i>As long as you carry out your role</i>
<i>as a bureaucrat to the very end.</i>

31:33.500 --> 31:36.625
I'm counting on you. Okay?

31:47.750 --> 31:48.791
I see.

31:49.916 --> 31:51.125
Thank you.

31:51.958 --> 31:52.958
TETSUSHI SASAKI LAW FIRM

31:53.041 --> 31:56.166
Ms. Matsuda told me
a little bit over the phone.

31:56.250 --> 31:58.333
What do you plan to do now?

32:00.875 --> 32:04.250
I was hoping I could take them to court.

32:04.916 --> 32:05.958
I see.

32:06.833 --> 32:09.708
I want everything
to come out into the open.

32:11.375 --> 32:13.791
Unless we can get to the root cause

32:14.791 --> 32:18.458
of why my husband was involved
in a cover-up, there's no point in this.

32:20.500 --> 32:21.833
I see.

32:25.333 --> 32:26.958
You don't think it can be done?

32:27.791 --> 32:29.916
This case was dropped once already,

32:30.000 --> 32:32.583
but it isn't completely impossible.

32:33.625 --> 32:36.208
If there is more definitive proof,
that could change things.

32:38.916 --> 32:41.916
You mean proof that
the prime minister was involved?

32:42.000 --> 32:42.875
Right.

32:44.458 --> 32:47.666
If this suicide note and memoir
are turned over to the public prosecutor,

32:47.750 --> 32:49.625
they might reopen the investigation.

32:50.125 --> 32:52.041
Would you like me to speak with them?

32:52.541 --> 32:54.125
Yes, I would appreciate that.

33:03.125 --> 33:05.208
<i>This situation has become exasperating.</i>

33:06.625 --> 33:09.208
They've really messed things up.

33:10.458 --> 33:12.458
If this public uproar continues,

33:12.541 --> 33:15.750
the public prosecutor could come
to question you, Murakami.

33:17.750 --> 33:18.625
I see.

33:18.708 --> 33:23.208
At any rate, we need to suppress
as much information as we can.

33:23.791 --> 33:24.708
Yes.

33:25.708 --> 33:27.291
But how can we do that?

33:27.375 --> 33:32.125
Now that there's such a commotion,
CIRO can't possibly deal with it alone.

33:32.958 --> 33:35.791
You can only do so much. Isn't that right?

33:36.833 --> 33:37.875
Well…

33:39.000 --> 33:43.125
We need someone of your status
to take action, Mr. Nakagawa.

33:44.125 --> 33:46.333
You did the same
for the Olympic bid, right?

33:47.458 --> 33:50.166
We'll get the heads
of every media outlet on our side.

33:50.250 --> 33:52.708
I'll get you in touch with them.
Let's do the same again.

33:53.666 --> 33:54.916
What should we do?

33:56.500 --> 33:59.291
Dig deep into the lives
of the media outlet heads.

34:00.500 --> 34:04.166
Find out all you can,
even about their families,

34:04.250 --> 34:05.666
no matter how trivial it is.

34:07.291 --> 34:09.583
It all depends on
how much dirt we can get on them.

34:10.541 --> 34:13.958
You'd like us
to tighten the screws on them?

34:15.000 --> 34:16.208
Immediately.

34:17.250 --> 34:18.208
Certainly.

34:35.416 --> 34:36.833
<i>…said in Parliament.</i>

34:36.916 --> 34:40.541
<i>National Property Administrator,</i>
<i>Supervisor Kurosaki,</i>

34:40.625 --> 34:42.541
<i>submitted the altered documents</i>

34:42.625 --> 34:44.958
<i>to Chubu Local</i>
<i>Finance Bureau Chief Mr. Kitano.</i>

34:46.291 --> 34:48.916
<i>On Monday, February 18,</i>

34:49.000 --> 34:50.208
<i>we were called together…</i>

34:50.291 --> 34:53.458
What do you think?

34:57.458 --> 35:02.000
Why wasn't everyone prosecuted
in the first place?

35:04.250 --> 35:07.500
I am not at liberty to answer that.

35:12.041 --> 35:14.500
However, before your husband died,

35:16.375 --> 35:18.583
I told him I could not ignore this case.

35:19.541 --> 35:20.416
What?

35:22.000 --> 35:23.333
I know it's a little late now,

35:25.166 --> 35:27.208
but now I feel like I could

35:29.041 --> 35:30.958
help with what Kazuya Suzuki wanted,

35:32.625 --> 35:34.416
which I wasn't able to do before.

35:41.208 --> 35:43.541
Thank you for these materials.

35:45.750 --> 35:47.750
I will perform a thorough investigation.

35:51.333 --> 35:53.125
TOUTO NEWS

35:53.208 --> 35:54.750
<i>Mr. Ryo Kinoshita.</i>

35:58.833 --> 36:01.625
I heard that you are
the nephew of Mr. Kazuya Suzuki.

36:04.416 --> 36:05.250
That's right.

36:06.208 --> 36:08.750
I also heard
you don't read the paper much.

36:11.708 --> 36:13.333
That's right. I'm sorry.

36:15.416 --> 36:19.666
If we hire you,
what kind of work would you like to do?

36:22.916 --> 36:23.958
For people like me

36:25.291 --> 36:30.875
who think the news doesn't concern them
or who have never read a newspaper,

36:31.833 --> 36:34.250
I'd like to write articles
that get them interested.

36:35.208 --> 36:37.208
I'd especially like to get young people

36:38.125 --> 36:41.625
to realize that what happens
in the world concerns them as well.

36:43.916 --> 36:46.208
That's the kind of journalist
I'd like to be.

36:50.166 --> 36:51.291
I'd also

36:52.708 --> 36:56.625
like to have fun
and make it my lifetime profession.

36:59.000 --> 36:59.958
Thank you.

37:07.000 --> 37:07.833
All right,

37:08.625 --> 37:10.958
can I ask you one more question?

37:11.875 --> 37:12.750
Certainly.

37:16.250 --> 37:20.458
How do you think
newspapers should adapt for the future?

37:44.708 --> 37:45.666
<i>Hello?</i>

37:46.166 --> 37:47.708
Hi, Mom.

37:47.791 --> 37:49.166
<i>Hi. What's up?</i>

37:52.583 --> 37:53.875
I got a job offer.

37:53.958 --> 37:55.541
Really? You did?

37:56.291 --> 37:57.125
<i>Yes.</i>

37:57.208 --> 37:59.250
I'll start work at Touto News in spring.

37:59.750 --> 38:02.833
<i>Really? Congratulations!</i>

38:02.916 --> 38:05.458
<i>So you'll be working with Ms. Matsuda?</i>

38:06.791 --> 38:07.791
Maybe.

38:09.041 --> 38:11.291
I don't know exactly
where I'll be assigned yet.

38:11.833 --> 38:13.000
<i>Oh, right.</i>

38:13.083 --> 38:14.750
Hold on. I'll put my sister on.

38:19.375 --> 38:20.750
Hello. Ryo?

38:22.500 --> 38:23.333
Congratulations.

38:23.416 --> 38:24.250
<i>Thank you.</i>

38:25.916 --> 38:27.875
Tell Uncle Kazuya for me.

38:29.583 --> 38:30.416
I will.

38:32.333 --> 38:33.375
Good luck.

38:35.291 --> 38:36.375
You too, Aunt Mayumi.

38:39.250 --> 38:40.375
Thank you.

38:40.458 --> 38:41.375
<i>Yeah.</i>

38:42.291 --> 38:44.458
<i>-Bye.</i>
-See you.

38:50.125 --> 38:51.708
What great news!

39:02.625 --> 39:07.250
FOUR MONTHS LATER

39:12.750 --> 39:14.708
-Good morning.
-Morning.

39:14.791 --> 39:16.583
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

39:19.000 --> 39:22.375
You two will be graduating soon,
won't you?

39:23.458 --> 39:25.916
No slacking off.
Keep working hard to the very end.

39:26.000 --> 39:27.708
-Okay.
-Yes, I know.

39:27.791 --> 39:33.041
It makes me happy to think that someday,
I'll deliver a paper written by Ryo.

39:34.208 --> 39:37.375
If you write garbage articles,
we'll poke fun at you here.

39:38.083 --> 39:41.291
-Just warning you.
-Oh, come on. Quit that.

39:49.833 --> 39:52.833
"First case of community spread
in Japan confirmed."

39:54.750 --> 39:55.583
What's wrong?

39:56.458 --> 40:00.583
Oh, it's just that there's been more news
about this lately. It worries me.

40:01.083 --> 40:03.125
That? We'll be just fine.

40:03.208 --> 40:05.958
They're making a big deal
out of nothing but a typical cold.

40:06.041 --> 40:09.000
Don't talk like that.
You need to be careful.

40:09.083 --> 40:10.666
Really?

40:33.916 --> 40:34.791
This looks fine.

40:35.833 --> 40:39.750
It won't be long before Mr. Nakagawa
starts meeting with these people.

40:39.833 --> 40:42.625
Make sure you complete
personal investigations of them by then.

40:45.833 --> 40:47.208
Mr. Tada.

40:50.500 --> 40:51.375
What is it?

40:54.166 --> 40:56.958
Do you really think investigating
the lives of private citizens

40:57.041 --> 40:59.958
and pressuring them
will help maintain national stability?

41:08.208 --> 41:09.916
What do you mean by that?

41:11.500 --> 41:13.916
Now that public opinion
has been swayed this far,

41:17.000 --> 41:19.041
it will be almost impossible to stop it.

41:19.125 --> 41:21.458
Since you directly requested
the discounted price from Mouri,

41:21.541 --> 41:24.875
do you think you can solve this
by apologizing to the citizens of Japan?

41:25.458 --> 41:26.458
Not at all.

41:28.791 --> 41:33.708
-I was just doing my job.
-You're wrong.

41:35.166 --> 41:38.833
This problem was caused because
you assumed what the First Lady wanted.

41:38.916 --> 41:41.958
If you hadn't
arbitrarily negotiated a discounted price,

41:42.041 --> 41:44.416
Mouri wouldn't have needed to resign,

41:44.500 --> 41:47.541
and the Chubu Local Finance Bureau
employee wouldn't have died,

41:47.625 --> 41:50.333
and this wouldn't have grown
into such a huge problem.

41:52.791 --> 41:54.291
What? I…

41:54.375 --> 41:55.375
Mr. Tada…

41:56.041 --> 41:57.125
All of this…

42:00.375 --> 42:03.208
was a scheme concocted by you alone.

42:07.458 --> 42:11.000
That's ridiculous. You must be kidding.

42:11.083 --> 42:13.500
Mr. Tada, I…

42:13.583 --> 42:17.458
It is possible to make that the truth.

42:24.750 --> 42:27.291
All you need to think about
is protecting the system.

42:27.791 --> 42:28.833
Get back to work.

42:34.416 --> 42:35.416
I'll go now.

42:43.000 --> 42:43.833
Wait.

42:45.083 --> 42:47.000
-One more thing, Murakami.
-Yes?

42:49.125 --> 42:53.541
The stability of your family is also
dependent on the stability of the nation.

43:18.833 --> 43:21.625
<i>This problem was caused because</i>
<i>you assumed what the First Lady wanted.</i>

43:21.708 --> 43:23.791
Daddy! Welcome home!

43:23.875 --> 43:26.541
-Welcome home!
-Thank you.

43:26.625 --> 43:30.541
<i>If you hadn't</i>
<i>arbitrarily negotiated a discounted price,</i>

43:31.041 --> 43:33.666
<i>Mouri wouldn't have needed to resign,</i>

43:34.291 --> 43:37.916
<i>and the Chubu Local Finance Bureau</i>
<i>employee wouldn't have died…</i>

43:38.666 --> 43:39.500
Yes, a rabbit.

43:39.583 --> 43:41.833
<i>…and this wouldn't have grown</i>
<i>into such a huge problem.</i>

43:41.916 --> 43:43.291
-A bear.
-A bear?

43:43.375 --> 43:44.333
<i>You're wrong.</i>

43:44.916 --> 43:45.791
<i>All of this</i>

43:46.666 --> 43:49.333
<i>was a scheme concocted by you alone.</i>

43:49.916 --> 43:50.750
No, I didn't.

44:04.125 --> 44:07.625
Hayato, you're spilling things.

44:10.333 --> 44:12.416
-Here. Wipe it up.
-Okay.

44:13.583 --> 44:15.000
Eat up your carrots.

44:43.250 --> 44:50.250
PHOTO SENT

44:58.333 --> 45:00.166
I KNOW YOUR BROTHER

45:03.958 --> 45:05.375
What is this?

45:15.583 --> 45:17.208
ARE YOU WITH THE PM'S OFFICE?

45:23.625 --> 45:26.333
ARE YOU WITH THE PM'S OFFICE?

